    • Method Detail

      • assign

        public org.objectweb.asm.tree.InsnList assign(IType input,
                                     IType output)
        This method determines whether a value of a type X can be converted to a value of a type Y, as is done during method invocations and variable assignments. Specifically, an assignment conversion is either a boxing conversion, an unboxing conversion, an identity conversion, an upcast, or a primitive coercion.
        Parameters:
        input - is the type of value that will be converted.
        output - is the type to convert the input value to.
        Returns:
        the bytecode that performs the actual conversion, or null, if no such conversion is possible.

      • checkArgs

        public <T extends IInvokableMember> java.util.List<T> checkArgs(java.util.List<T> members,
                                                       java.util.List<? extends IType> arguments)
        Given the types of the arguments in an arguments-list and a set of invokable members, this method selects those invokable members whose formal-parameter types are acceptable matches for the given arguments.

        A method will be selected, if each argument X is convertible to the related formal-parameter type P, using an assignment conversion.

        Parameters:
        members - is the list invokable members to choose from.
        arguments - are the types of the arguments.
        Returns:
        a list containing the selected members.

      • forceAssign

        public void forceAssign(org.objectweb.asm.tree.InsnList code,
               IExpressionType target,
               IReferenceType value)
        This method generates bytecode that assigns a reference-type to another, possibly primitive, type.

        If the target is a primitive-type, the generated code is a cast to the related boxed-type and then an unboxing operation.

        Parameters:
        code - is the code being generated.
        target - is the type of the assignee.
        value - is the type of the value being assigned to the assignee.
